HEADWORD: Rockaway
<hw>Rock"a*way</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[Probably from
<ets>Rockaway</ets> beach, where it was used.]</ety> <def>Formerly, a
light, low, four-wheeled carriage, with standing top, open at the sides,
but having waterproof curtains which could be let down when occasion
required; now, a somewhat similar, but heavier, carriage, inclosed,
except in front, and having a door at each side.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

